-- CROP CULTIVATION PRACTICES (TELUGU)
-- ===========================================

('అధునాతన వరి సాగు పద్ధతులు', 'వరి ప్రపంచ జనాభాలో సగానికి మించిన వారి ప్రధాన ఆహారం. అధునాతన సాగులో ఇవి ఉంటాయి: 1) సమానమైన నీటి పంపిణీ కోసం లేజర్ లెవలింగ్‌తో భూమి తయారీ, 2) బాస్మతి 370, పిఆర్-126, లేదా హైబ్రిడ్ రకాలు వంటి అధిక దిగుబడినిచ్చే రకాల ఎంపిక, 3) ప్రత్యక్ష విత్తనాలు లేదా 21-25 రోజుల మొలకల నాటడం, 4) వృక్ష వృద్ధి సమయంలో 2-5 సెం.మీ నీటి లోతు నిర్వహణ, 5) నత్రజని విభజిత వాడకం (50% మూల, 25% కొమ్మల వేళ, 25% వెంట్రుకల వేళ), 6) ఫెరోమోన్ ట్రాప్స్, జీవసంబంధమైన నియంత్రణ, మరియు అవసరం ఆధారిత పురుగుమందుల వాడకంతో సమగ్ర పురుగుల నిర్వహణ, 7) 80% పరిపక్వతలో కోత ధాన్యాలు బంగారు పసుపు రంగులోకి మారినప్పుడు, 8) నిల్వ కోసం 14% తేమ వరకు సరైన ఎండబెట్టడం।', 'crops', 'rice', 'te', ARRAY['వరి', 'సాగు', 'నీటిపారుదల', 'ఎరువులు', 'కోత']),

('గోధుమ ఉత్పాదన నిర్వహణ', 'గోధుమ ఒక ప్రధాన ధాన్య పంట ప్రత్యేక నిర్వహణ అవసరం: 1) లోతైన దున్నిన తర్వాత మట్టి తయారీ, 2) రకం ఆధారంగా అక్టోబర్ 15 - నవంబర్ 30 మధ్య విత్తన సమయ అనుకూలత, 3) సమయానికి విత్తనం కోసం 100-125 కిలోలు/హెక్టేర్, ఆలస్య విత్తనం కోసం 150 కిలోలు/హెక్టేర్ విత్తన రేటు, 4) గరిష్ఠ ఉత్పాదనకు 18-23 సెం.మీ వరుస అంతరం, 5) కీలక దశలలో నీటిపారుదల: మూల ఏర్పాటు (20-25 రోజులు), కొమ్మల దశ (40-45 రోజులు), గాంటు దశ (60-65 రోజులు), పుట్టుట (85-90 రోజులు), మరియు ధాన్య నింపుట (105-110 రోజులు), 6) 120:60:40 ఎన్‌పికె కిలోలు/హెక్టేర్‌తో సమతులిత ఎరువుల వాడకం, 7) మొలకెత్తే ముందు కలుపు నిర్మూలకాలు లేదా చేతితో కలుపుల నిర్వహణ, 8) నిరోధక రకాలు మరియు శిలీంధ్రనాశకాలతో తుప్పు, స్మట్, మరియు బంట్ వ్యాధుల నియంత్రణ।', 'crops', 'wheat', 'te', ARRAY['గోధుమ', 'విత్తనం', 'నీటిపారుదల', 'ఎరువులు', 'వ్యాధుల-నిర్వహణ']),

-- ===========================================
-- PEST AND DISEASE MANAGEMENT
-- ===========================================

-- Integrated Pest Management
('Integrated Pest Management Strategies', 'IPM is a holistic approach combining multiple pest control methods: 1) Cultural control through crop rotation, intercropping with marigold, trap crops, and sanitation, 2) Biological control using natural predators like ladybird beetles, lacewings, parasitic wasps, and microbial agents like Bacillus thuringiensis, 3) Mechanical control through pheromone traps, light traps, and physical barriers, 4) Chemical control as the last resort using selective, low-toxicity pesticides with proper rotation to prevent resistance, 5) Monitoring through regular field scouting, yellow and blue sticky traps, and threshold-based intervention, 6) Resistance management by alternating pesticide modes of action and using tank mixtures, 7) Farmer education and training for proper identification of pests and beneficial insects.', 'pest-management', 'IPM', 'en', ARRAY['IPM', 'biological-control', 'pheromone-traps', 'pesticide-rotation', 'threshold']),

-- Disease Management
('Plant Disease Diagnosis and Management', 'Effective disease management requires accurate diagnosis and timely intervention: 1) Visual symptoms identification: leaf spots, wilting, stunting, discoloration, and growth abnormalities, 2) Laboratory diagnosis using microscopy, serology, and molecular techniques for confirmation, 3) Cultural practices: crop rotation, sanitation, resistant varieties, and proper spacing for air circulation, 4) Chemical control: preventive and curative fungicide applications with proper timing and coverage, 5) Biological control using antagonistic microorganisms like Trichoderma, Pseudomonas, and Bacillus species, 6) Environmental manipulation: adjusting humidity, temperature, and irrigation to create unfavorable conditions for pathogens, 7) Quarantine measures to prevent introduction and spread of new diseases, 8) Record keeping for monitoring disease pressure and treatment efficacy.', 'diseases', 'management', 'en', ARRAY['disease-diagnosis', 'fungicides', 'biological-control', 'quarantine', 'monitoring']),

-- ===========================================
-- SOIL AND FERTILITY MANAGEMENT
-- ===========================================

('Soil Health Assessment and Improvement', 'Soil health is fundamental to sustainable agriculture: 1) Physical assessment: structure, texture, bulk density, water infiltration, and compaction levels, 2) Chemical analysis: pH, electrical conductivity, organic matter, available nutrients (NPK, secondary, and micronutrients), 3) Biological indicators: soil respiration, microbial biomass, enzyme activity, and earthworm population, 4) Improvement strategies: organic matter addition through compost, vermicompost, and crop residues, 5) Cover cropping with legumes and grasses to improve soil structure and nitrogen fixation, 6) Reduced tillage practices to maintain soil structure and increase water retention, 7) Balanced fertilization based on soil test recommendations and crop requirements, 8) Lime application to correct soil acidity and gypsum for alkali soils, 9) Bio-fertilizers containing nitrogen-fixing bacteria, phosphate-solubilizing bacteria, and mycorrhizal fungi.', 'soil', 'health', 'en', ARRAY['soil-testing', 'organic-matter', 'cover-crops', 'bio-fertilizers', 'pH-management']),

('Nutrient Management Planning', 'Scientific nutrient management for optimal crop nutrition: 1) Soil testing for baseline nutrient status and pH determination, 2) Crop nutrient requirement assessment based on target yield and nutrient uptake patterns, 3) Nutrient budgeting considering soil supply, organic sources, and fertilizer requirements, 4) 4R nutrient stewardship: Right source, Right rate, Right time, Right place, 5) Organic nutrient sources: farmyard manure, compost, vermicompost, green manure, and bio-fertilizers, 6) Inorganic fertilizer selection and timing: split application for nitrogen, basal application for phosphorus and potassium, 7) Micronutrient management through soil and foliar applications, 8) Precision agriculture tools: variable rate application, soil sensors, and satellite imagery for site-specific management, 9) Environmental considerations: minimizing leaching, runoff, and greenhouse gas emissions.', 'soil', 'fertility', 'en', ARRAY['soil-testing', '4R-stewardship', 'organic-fertilizers', 'precision-agriculture', 'environmental-protection']),

-- ===========================================
-- WATER MANAGEMENT AND IRRIGATION
-- ===========================================

('Efficient Irrigation Management', 'Water-efficient irrigation for sustainable agriculture: 1) Irrigation scheduling based on crop water requirement, soil moisture, and weather conditions, 2) Drip irrigation systems for precision water and fertigation delivery, 3) Sprinkler irrigation for uniform water distribution in field crops, 4) Mulching for moisture conservation and evaporation reduction, 5) Rainwater harvesting and storage in farm ponds and check dams, 6) Deficit irrigation strategies for water-scarce regions, 7) Soil moisture monitoring using tensiometers, soil sensors, and gravimetric methods, 8) Irrigation water quality assessment for salinity, sodicity, and chemical contamination, 9) Drainage systems for waterlogged areas and salt management, 10) Crop selection and variety choice based on water availability and drought tolerance.', 'water-management', 'irrigation', 'en', ARRAY['drip-irrigation', 'irrigation-scheduling', 'water-conservation', 'rainwater-harvesting', 'drought-tolerance']),

-- ===========================================
-- LIVESTOCK MANAGEMENT
-- ===========================================

('Dairy Cattle Nutrition and Management', 'Comprehensive dairy cattle management for optimal milk production: 1) Balanced nutrition with quality fodder: green fodder (20-25 kg), dry fodder (4-6 kg), and concentrate (1 kg per 2.5 kg milk), 2) Breeding management: artificial insemination, heat detection, and genetic improvement programs, 3) Health care: vaccination schedule, deworming, hoof trimming, and mastitis prevention, 4) Housing requirements: adequate space (3.5 sq.m per animal), ventilation, and cleanliness, 5) Milking hygiene: clean udder washing, proper milking technique, and rapid cooling, 6) Calf management: colostrum feeding, weaning strategies, and growth monitoring, 7) Record keeping: breeding, health, production, and financial records, 8) Pasture management: rotational grazing and fodder crop cultivation, 9) Waste management: biogas production and organic manure preparation.', 'livestock', 'dairy', 'en', ARRAY['dairy-nutrition', 'breeding', 'mastitis-prevention', 'milking-hygiene', 'record-keeping']),

('Poultry Production Management', 'Modern poultry farming for sustainable egg and meat production: 1) Housing systems: battery cages for layers, deep litter for broilers, and free-range for organic production, 2) Nutrition management: starter, grower, and finisher feeds with appropriate protein and energy levels, 3) Health management: vaccination programs, biosecurity measures, and disease prevention protocols, 4) Environmental control: temperature, humidity, ventilation, and lighting programs, 5) Breeding: selection for production traits, artificial insemination, and genetic improvement, 6) Egg handling: collection, cleaning, grading, and storage at optimal conditions, 7) Meat processing: humane slaughter, processing hygiene, and cold chain maintenance, 8) Waste management: litter composting and biogas production, 9) Marketing strategies: direct sales, cooperative marketing, and value addition.', 'livestock', 'poultry', 'en', ARRAY['poultry-housing', 'nutrition', 'vaccination', 'biosecurity', 'egg-handling']),

-- ===========================================
-- AGRICULTURAL TECHNOLOGY AND INNOVATION
-- ===========================================

('Precision Agriculture Technologies', 'Technology-driven farming for enhanced efficiency and sustainability: 1) GPS-guided tractors and machinery for precise field operations, 2) Variable rate technology for optimized input application based on field variability, 3) Remote sensing using satellites and drones for crop monitoring and yield estimation, 4) Soil sensors for real-time monitoring of moisture, nutrients, and pH, 5) Weather stations and forecasting systems for informed decision making, 6) Farm management software for record keeping, planning, and financial analysis, 7) Internet of Things (IoT) devices for automation and monitoring, 8) Artificial intelligence and machine learning for predictive analytics, 9) Robotic systems for planting, weeding, and harvesting, 10) Blockchain technology for supply chain traceability and food safety.', 'technology', 'precision-agriculture', 'en', ARRAY['GPS-guidance', 'variable-rate-technology', 'remote-sensing', 'IoT', 'artificial-intelligence']),

('Digital Agriculture and Smart Farming', 'Digital transformation in agriculture for the 21st century farmer: 1) Mobile applications for crop advisory, weather information, and market prices, 2) Cloud computing for data storage, processing, and accessibility, 3) Big data analytics for pattern recognition and decision support, 4) Autonomous vehicles and machinery for reduced labor dependency, 5) Sensor networks for comprehensive farm monitoring, 6) Decision support systems integrating multiple data sources, 7) E-commerce platforms for input procurement and produce marketing, 8) Digital financial services for credit access and insurance, 9) Virtual reality and augmented reality for training and education, 10) Cyber security measures for protecting farm data and systems.', 'technology', 'digital-agriculture', 'en', ARRAY['mobile-apps', 'cloud-computing', 'big-data', 'autonomous-vehicles', 'decision-support-systems']),

-- ===========================================
-- CLIMATE CHANGE AND ADAPTATION
-- ===========================================

('Climate Change Adaptation Strategies', 'Building resilience against climate change impacts: 1) Drought-tolerant crop varieties and stress-resistant cultivars, 2) Water conservation through micro-irrigation and rainwater harvesting, 3) Climate-smart agriculture practices for carbon sequestration, 4) Diversified farming systems to reduce risk and improve stability, 5) Early warning systems for weather-related hazards, 6) Crop insurance and risk management strategies, 7) Soil health improvement for better water retention and nutrient cycling, 8) Agroforestry systems for microclimate modification and additional income, 9) Greenhouse and protected cultivation for controlled environment, 10) Community-based adaptation programs and farmer knowledge networks.', 'climate', 'adaptation', 'en', ARRAY['drought-tolerance', 'water-conservation', 'climate-smart-agriculture', 'risk-management', 'agroforestry']),

-- ===========================================
-- POST-HARVEST MANAGEMENT AND VALUE ADDITION
-- ===========================================

('Post-Harvest Management and Processing', 'Reducing post-harvest losses and adding value to farm produce: 1) Timely harvesting at optimum maturity for maximum quality and shelf life, 2) Proper cleaning, grading, and sorting to remove damaged and inferior produce, 3) Appropriate drying methods: sun drying, mechanical drying, and solar drying, 4) Storage management: pest control, moisture monitoring, and temperature regulation, 5) Processing technologies: milling, oil extraction, and food processing for value addition, 6) Packaging in suitable materials for protection and marketing appeal, 7) Cold chain management for perishable commodities, 8) Quality control and food safety measures throughout the supply chain, 9) Marketing channels: direct marketing, farmer producer organizations, and e-commerce platforms, 10) Certification programs: organic, fair trade, and geographical indications for premium pricing.', 'post-harvest', 'processing', 'en', ARRAY['harvesting', 'drying', 'storage', 'processing', 'cold-chain', 'marketing']),

-- ===========================================
-- AGRICULTURAL ECONOMICS AND MARKETING
-- ===========================================

('Farm Economics and Financial Management', 'Economic principles for profitable and sustainable farming: 1) Cost of production analysis including fixed and variable costs, 2) Enterprise budgeting for different crops and livestock activities, 3) Break-even analysis to determine minimum production levels, 4) Cash flow management for seasonal income patterns, 5) Credit management: sources, terms, and repayment strategies, 6) Insurance coverage for crops, livestock, and farm assets, 7) Investment analysis for machinery, infrastructure, and technology adoption, 8) Market analysis and price forecasting for informed production decisions, 9) Value chain analysis to identify profit opportunities, 10) Record keeping and financial planning for long-term sustainability.', 'economics', 'financial-management', 'en', ARRAY['cost-analysis', 'budgeting', 'credit-management', 'insurance', 'market-analysis']),

('Agricultural Marketing and Supply Chain', 'Effective marketing strategies for better farm income: 1) Market research and demand analysis for crop selection and planning, 2) Quality standards and grading systems for premium pricing, 3) Direct marketing through farmers markets and community-supported agriculture, 4) Cooperative marketing for collective bargaining and reduced transaction costs, 5) Contract farming for assured markets and stable prices, 6) Online platforms and e-commerce for wider market reach, 7) Export opportunities and quality compliance for international markets, 8) Value addition through processing and branding, 9) Supply chain optimization for reduced costs and improved efficiency, 10) Government schemes and support programs for marketing assistance.', 'economics', 'marketing', 'en', ARRAY['market-research', 'quality-standards', 'cooperative-marketing', 'contract-farming', 'value-addition']);
